The paper deals with the problem of f-divergence estimation, which is a topic in machine learning, information theory, and statistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses divergence-based inference tasks such as testing equality of pairs of distributions based on empirical samples, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
